.SH NAME
timeit \- time command execution
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]timeit\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[B]\(en\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R]
[\f[I]args\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs \f[I]command\f[R] and reports wall\-clock time, CPU time, peak
memory usage, and exit code.
.PP
A transparent wrapper \(em the child\(cqs stdout, stderr, and exit code
pass through unmodified.
Summary output goes to stderr by default, so it does not pollute piped
command output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
